"Vargas G., Pantoja S., Rutllant J.A., Lange C.B., Ortlieb L.","Enhancement of coastal upwelling and interdecadal ENSO-like variability in the Peru-Chile Current since late 19th century",2007,"Geophysical Research Letters","34","13", L13607,"","",,,10.1029/2006GL028812,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34548619647&partnerID=40&md5=15ef5b5f9cc88390b1e1718010969138","Department of Geology, University of Chile, Plaza Ercilla 803, Santiago, Chile; Department of Oceanography, Center for Oceanographic Research in the Eastern South Pacific, University of Concepción, Casilla 160-C, Concepción, Chile; Department of Geophysics, University of Chile, Blanco Encalada 2002, Santiago, Chile; Département de Paléotropique, Institut de Recherche pour le Développement, 32 Avenue Henri Varagnat, F-93143 Bondy, France","Vargas, G., Department of Geology, University of Chile, Plaza Ercilla 803, Santiago, Chile; Pantoja, S., Department of Oceanography, Center for Oceanographic Research in the Eastern South Pacific, University of Concepción, Casilla 160-C, Concepción, Chile; Rutllant, J.A., Department of Geophysics, University of Chile, Blanco Encalada 2002, Santiago, Chile; Lange, C.B., Department of Oceanography, Center for Oceanographic Research in the Eastern South Pacific, University of Concepción, Casilla 160-C, Concepción, Chile; Ortlieb, L., Département de Paléotropique, Institut de Recherche pour le Développement, 32 Avenue Henri Varagnat, F-93143 Bondy, France","Secular trends in coastal upwelling proxies from a sediment record at 23°S encompassing 250 years reveal two distinct stages separated by a transition period between AD 1820 and 1878. Persistent interdecadal variability that roughly follows the Pacific Decadal Oscillation is accompanied by intensification of upwelling-favourable coastal winds and decreased coastal sea surface temperature since AD 1878. We propose that an increased land-sea thermal contrast along the and coast of northern Chile and Peru intensifies the equatorward wind stress due to reduced mean low-cloud cover, resulting in enhanced primary and export production during interdecadal El Niño-like conditions. This mechanism overcompensates for the overall effect of a regional surface warming secular trend in the Peru-Chile Current System, providing a novel insight on physical and biogeochemical feedbacks of coastal upwelling ecosystems to global warming. Copyright 2007 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Atmospheric temperature; Coastal zones; Global warming; Sediments; Wind; Wind stress; Coastal upwelling; Interdecadal variability; Sea surface temperature; Surface warming; Ocean currents; coastal current; decadal variation; El Nino-Southern Oscillation; global warming; nearshore dynamics; nineteenth century; Pacific Decadal Oscillation; sea surface temperature; secular variation; upwelling; Chile; Peru; South America",,,,,,"Bakun, A., Global climate change and intensification of coastal ocean upwelling (1990) Science, 247, pp. 198-201; Berger, W.H., Appendix global maps of ocean productivity (1988) Productivity of the Ocean: Present and Past, pp. 429-455. , edited by W. H. Berger, V. S. Smetacek, and G. Wefer, pp, John Wiley, Hoboken, N. J; Brown, T.A., Farwell, G.W., Grootes, P.M., Schmidt, F.H., Stuiver, M., Intra-annual variability of the radiocarbon content of corals from the Galapagos Islands (1993) Radiocarbon, 35, pp. 245-251; Carr, M.E., Strub, P.T., Thomas, A.C., Blanco, J.L., Evolution of 1996-1999 La Niña and El Niño conditions off western coast of South America: A remote sensing perspective (2002) J. Geophys. Res, 107 (C12), p. 3236. , doi:10.1029/2001JC001183; Daneri, G., Dellarossa, V., Quiñones, R., Jacob, B., Montero, P., Ulloa, O., Primary production and community respiration in the Humboldt Current System off Chile and associated oceanic areas (2000) Mar. Ecol. Prog. Ser, 197, pp. 41-49; Enfield, D., Thermally driven wind variability in the planetary boundary layer above Lima, Per